<p><strong>Ruins Greatsword</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Colossal Swords" href="/Colossal+Swords" target="">Colossal Sword</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Ruins Greatsword</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence">Intelligence</a> and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for its additional magic damage.&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Originally rubble from a ruin which fell from the sky, this surviving fragment was honed into a weapon.<br>One of the legendary armaments.</em></p> 
 <p><em>The ruin it came from crumbled when struck by a meteorite, as such this weapon harbors its destructive power.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Ruins Greatsword in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Ruins Greatsword weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Ruins Greatsword can be acquried by defeating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Misbegotten Warrior" href="/Misbegotten+Warrior" target="">Misbegotten Warrior</a>&nbsp;+ <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Crucible Knight" href="/Crucible+Knight" target="">Crucible Knight</a>&nbsp;at Redmane Castle Plaza. [<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=6203&amp;lat=-193.05469&amp;lng=159.48091&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=6203&amp;lat=-193.05469&amp;lng=159.48091&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map here</a>] This boss fight is only accessible before the festival&nbsp;OR&nbsp;after defeating&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Starscourge Radahn" href="/Starscourge+Radahn">Starscourge Radahn</a> and exhausting&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Witch-Hunter Jerren" href="/Witch-Hunter+Jerren">Witch-Hunter Jerren</a>'s&nbsp;subsequent dialogue. <a class="wiki_link" title="Video Location" href="https://youtu.be/CHhUzkuyDh8?t=966">Video Location</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Ruins Greatsword Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wave of Destruction" href="/Wave+of+Destruction" target="">Wave of Destruction</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon cannot be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War<br></a></li> 
 <li>Cannot be enchanted with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells">Magic</a> nor boosted by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables">Consumables</a></li> 
 <li><strong>Ruins Greatsword</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Wave of Destruction: The weapon skill damage scales primarily with weapon level. There are minor increases in damage from STR levels, and the least increase from INT levels.</li> 
 <li>Charged strong attacks cause a small burst of gravity magic upon slamming the&nbsp;ground. This slam causes additional damage,&nbsp;as well as staggering enemies in close proximity. This doesn't cost FP, but consumes more Stamina than normal charged heavy attacks.</li> 
 <li>If the player doesn't meet the stat requirements to wield the weapon, the following penalties are applied:<br> 
  <ul> 
   <li>They will become unable to use the Weapon Skill.</li> 
   <li>Their stamina cost on each attack is increased.</li> 
   <li>They cannot benefit from the weapon's magic scaling.</li> 
   <li>However, meeting the STR requirement allows the physical damage and scaling of the weapon remain the same. The base magical damage also remains unaffected.<br> 
    <ul> 
     <li>This could prove useful for pure Strength builds if the player manages to acquire it early in the game, provided they can find the Somber Stones to upgrade it.</li> 
    </ul> </li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;1000</li> 
 <li>Normally you can rotate to attack in any which direction during the final stages of the animation but with this weapon the 1H R2 is seemingly locked into whatever direction you were facing when pressing R2. (This bug been patched as of 1.07)</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Moveset &amp; Videos in&nbsp;Elden Ring for&nbsp;Ruins Greatsword</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Videos for the Ruins Greatsword Coming Soon</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Ruins Greatsword Upgrades in Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>Please see the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Upgrades" href="/Upgrades" target="">Upgrades</a>&nbsp;page to understand the weapon bolstering process.</p> 
<p>Requires regular reinforcement with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Somber Smithing Stones" href="/Somber+Smithing+Stones" target="">Somber Smithing Stones</a>.</p> 
<p>This weapon cannot be enchanted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Magic Spells" href="/Magic+Spells" target="">Magic</a>&nbsp;or boosted with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Consumables" href="/Consumables" target="">Consumables</a>.</p> 
