				<li id="16724419" class="cmnt-root" data="4" data-d="1656310552000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579028/Ruins-Greatsword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">27 Jun 2022 02:15</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16724419" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I had trouble getting this weapon at first, but finally succeeded (easily) by using the greatshield ashes +3. Basically this fight obviously should not be done before killing Radahn since the festival makes it so trivial to get to the site of grace, and also makes it much easier to do non-festival castle since you&apos;re already inside, working backwards.<br/><br/>Anyway, with Radahn dead, go into Nokron. You&apos;ll face very weak easy enemies and will come across the greatshield ashes very quickly (no boss fights). Get them, upgrade to +3, and it will do wonders to help with this fight. I was level 60 using a grafted dragon +4.<br/><br/>As for this weapon, it&apos;s awesome. Its range is much longer than you&apos;d expect, and wide, and a single cast can wipe out a ton of ordinary enemies, and knocks down most that survive. For the latter reason, I found it very helpful against NPC invaders as well. I&apos;ve also used it on bosses to great effect; it doesn&apos;t knock the large ones down of course but it does heavy damage from range and the cast time is very fast. And the effects just look awesome.<br/><br/>It&apos;s also surprisingly good for blocking when two-handed.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16724419" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16724419" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>4</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16724419"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16724419" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16724419"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
